report_text: left-sided pacemaker device is noted with leads terminating in the right atrium and right ventricle . moderate cardiomegaly is re- demonstrated . the aorta is diffusely calcified and tortuous . mediastinal and hilar contours are unchanged . pulmonary vasculature is not engorged . lungs are hyperinflated without focal consolidation . no pleural effusion or pneumothorax is present . there are no acute osseous abnormalities .
